The paper deals with algorithmic problems on directed hypergraphs and their strongly connected components, which are topics related to data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The motivation for studying this problem comes from a recent application of directed hypergraphs to computational tropical geometry, which falls under discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the complexity of the algorithm, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper mentions the use of graph theory in their approach, which is related to graph theory (cs.GT).
